  "bug_report_content": "Title: ListPopulation Iterator allows you to remove chromosomes from the population.\nType: Bug | Priority: Major | Status: Closed | Resolution: Fixed\n\nDescription:\nCalling the iterator method of ListPopulation returns an iterator of the protected modifiable list. Before returning the iterator we should wrap it in an unmodifiable list.\n\nComments:\n\n[Reid Hochstedler]: Proposed patch.\n\n[Thomas Neidhart]: Fixed in r1325427 with minor modifications (updated javadoc, use getChromosomes() instead of Collections.unmodifiableList).",
  "fix_diff": "--- org.apache.commons.math3.genetics.ListPopulation (buggy)\n+++ org.apache.commons.math3.genetics.ListPopulation (fixed)\n@@ -206,6 +206,6 @@\n      * @return chromosome iterator\n      */\n     public Iterator<Chromosome> iterator() {\n-        return chromosomes.iterator();\n+        return getChromosomes().iterator();\n     }\n }"
